    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen I try to build a Cython Extension with Python3.12 on Windows, I get:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  py_gd.obj : error LNK2001: unresolved external symbol PyUnicode_AsUnicode\r\n  build\\lib.win-amd64-cpython-312\\py_gd\\py_gd.cp312-win_amd64.pyd : fatal error LNK1120: 1 unresolved externals\r\n  error: command 'C:\\\\Program Files\\\\Microsoft Visual \r\n```\r\n\r\nI understand that `PyUnicode_AsUnicode` has been deprecated, and maybe hav been removed in 3.12 -- but this is the latest Cython (and recent!) -- and it does build just fine on OS-X and Linux. \r\n\r\ncython-3.0.9 (from conda-forge)\r\n\r\nI don't have a windows machine handy -- this is failing on the gitHub CI, but everything looks right, and the Windows builds for 3.9, 3.10, 3.11 all seem to work.\r\n\r\nHere's the CI log:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NOAA-ORR-ERD/py_gd/actions/runs/8179565237/job/22367116577\r\n\r\n\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\n# example code\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\nWindows\n\n### Python version\n\nPython 3.12.2\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.9\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
